# arci-tutorial-delivery

**Read:** [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), [README.md](../../README.md) (section Agent tutorial delivery).

**`[clarify]`:** Delegate to subagent [clarify](../agents/clarify.md) per [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Step how-to → numbered README actions first ([clarify.md](../agents/clarify.md) Lesson-step requests).

**`[explain]`:** Delegate to subagent [explain](../agents/explain.md) per [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md); on user confirmation to persist a gap, chain Task → `clarify` with the handoff block from `explain`.

**Tone / format:** Short clear sentences; multi-part fit → bullets or blank lines ([AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) Readability). Verbatim closing phrase in AGENTS (Tone and explanations).

## MUST — teaching frame

**Trigger:** User asks where they are, what is next, how to resume, or equivalent.

**Include before/with checklist:**

1. Next CAD target (body / sketch / spreadsheet / feature) in plain terms.
2. Assembly fit: Pi (module 02) vs bezel (03) vs shell (05) + real part; cite [architecture.md](../../architecture.md), [component_specs.md](../../component_specs.md) as needed.

**Forbidden:** Checklist-only or alias-only reply (e.g. only `Screen_W = 165`) without the frame.

## End of each lesson step

After step actions: request screenshot (main window + model tree + 3D view; task panel / constraints if relevant; FreeCAD version if known). Check the user is in a good spot before the next step. Full spec: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) (End of each lesson step, FreeCAD UI — screenshots).
